text: Fővárosi Testedzők Köre was a Hungarian football club from the town of Budapest. ==History== Fővárosi Testedzők Köre debuted in the 1916-17 season of the Hungarian League and finished ninth. == Name Changes == *1909-1949: Fővárosi Testedzők Köre *1922: merger with Acél Torna Egylet *1926: foundation of a new club, Zuglói VII. Kerületi AC as Turul FC *1949: merger with Magyar Acél SE == References == ==External links== * Profile Category:Football clubs in Hungary Category:1909 establishments in Hungary Category:Association football clubs established in 1909 Category:Association football clubs disestablished in 1949 Category:1949 disestablishments in Hungary
